# mstack repository memory

When editing **this repository** (not only consuming rules elsewhere), use the docs as **long-term memory**:

1. **[docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md](../../docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md)** — what the repo is, where to look, glossary.
2. **[docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)** — directory roles, API lifecycle, endpoints, env vars.
3. **[docs/DECISIONS.md](../../docs/DECISIONS.md)** — why key choices were made; **append** when you change behavior or layout.

## Maintenance rule

If you change **HTTP routes**, **env vars**, **invariants** of the Ideas API, or **folder purpose**, update `ARCHITECTURE.md` and add a dated bullet to `DECISIONS.md` in the same change (or immediately after).

For **mstack-only** edits (rules/templates), a short `DECISIONS.md` note is enough when the change affects how agents should behave globally.
